Court will consider for early release of probation AND expungement if defendant successfully completes all conditions of probation with no new law violations reaching the level of a probable cause finding.

Statements made as to Sentencing by both counsel and Defendant.

COURT SENTENCED Defendant to serve 3 MONTHS, STRAIGHT TIME, in the House of Correction with credit for 1 day time served.  

Court IMPOSED AND STAYED the sentence and placed Defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 YEAR with the following conditions:
*  No new law violations reaching the level of a probable cause finding.
*  Cooperate with agent.
*  Pay costs, surcharges, assessments, supervision, DNA fees out of bail, if any, on deposit with the balance due on or before the probationary period.  Failure to pay shall result in a Civil Judgment with tax intercept.
*  Community service of 25 hours.
*  Defendant required to provide a biological specimen (DNA) to the State Crime Lab for testing.
*  Participate in parenting classes.

Court will consider for early release of probation AND expungement if Defendant successfully completes all conditions of probation with no new law violations reaching the level of a probable cause finding.
